- **Component File Structure:**
  - One component per file
  - Use PascalCase for component names and file names
  - Export default for main component
  - Export types/interfaces if used externally

- **Component Patterns:**
  ```tsx
  // ✅ DO: Standard component structure
  'use client' // Only if needed (hooks, state, browser APIs)
  
  import { useState } from 'react'
  import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
  
  interface ComponentProps {
    title: string
    optional?: boolean
  }
  
  export default function ComponentName({ title, optional }: ComponentProps) {
    const [state, setState] = useState('')
    
    return (
      <div className="...">
        {/* Component content */}
      </div>
    )
  }
  ```

- **UI Component Pattern (shadcn/ui style):**
  - UI components in `components/ui/` directory
  - Use `forwardRef` for DOM ref forwarding
  - Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
  - Extend HTML element props
  ```tsx
  // ✅ DO: UI component pattern (see [button.tsx](mdc:components/ui/button.tsx))
  import * as React from "react"
  import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
  
  export interface ButtonProps
    extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
    variant?: "default" | "outline" | "ghost" | "link"
  }
  
  const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
    ({ className, variant = "default", ...props }, ref) => {
      return (
        <button
          className={cn(
            "base-classes",
            variant === "default" && "variant-classes",
            className
          )}
          ref={ref}
          {...props}
        />
      )
    }
  )
  Button.displayName = "Button"
  
  export { Button }
  ```

- **Styling Guidelines:**
  - Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
  - Use `cn()` for conditional/merged classes
  - Follow existing color scheme:
    - Primary: `blue-600`, `blue-700` (hover)
    - Background: `slate-50`, `blue-50`, `slate-100` (gradients)
    - Text: `slate-900`, `slate-700`, `slate-600`
    - Borders: `gray-200`, `gray-300`
  
  ```tsx
  // ✅ DO: Consistent styling
  className={cn(
    "base-classes",
    condition && "conditional-classes",
    className // Allow override
  )}
  ```

- **Responsive Design:**
  - Mobile-first approach
  - Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
  - Common patterns:
    - `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8` for horizontal padding
    - `text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl` for responsive text
    - `grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` for responsive grids

- **Component Composition:**
  - Break down complex components into smaller, reusable pieces
  - Keep components focused on a single responsibility
  - Use composition over configuration when possible

- **Props Interface:**
